  "prompt": "How do say \"I love you\" in Spanish?",
  "response": "In Spanish, \"I love you\" can be expressed in two main ways:\n\n1. **Te quiero**  \n   - **Usage:** Commonly used among family members, friends, and in romantic relationships. It's a versatile phrase that conveys affection and care.\n   \n2. **Te amo**  \n   - **Usage:** Typically reserved for deep, passionate romantic love. It's often used in more serious or intense relationships.\n\n**Example Sentences:**\n- *Te quiero mucho.* (I love you a lot.)\n- *Te amo con todo mi coraz\u00f3n.* (I love you with all my heart.)\n\nChoose the phrase that best fits the context of your relationship and the depth of your feelings.",
